# Form Select / Dropdown Standard

Applies to **every** `<Select>`, `ErpSmartSelect`, and native `<select>` used as a form or filter control.

## Rules

1. **Closed state** — When nothing is chosen, show placeholder **`— Select —`** (constant `SELECT_PLACEHOLDER` from `frontend/src/components/forms/selectStandards.ts`). Field-specific copy like `Select vendor…` is OK; bare `Select…` / `Choose…` must normalize to `— Select —`.
2. **Options only on open** — Do not render choice lists as always-visible chips/radios unless the UX is explicitly multi-select toggles. Use `Select` / `ErpSmartSelect` so data appears **after click or focus**.
3. **Empty option** — First option is `<option value="">…</option>` (or smart-select `allowEmpty`). Never rely on the first real row as the “unselected” state.
4. **Open list** — Exclude the empty placeholder from the dropdown list; show only real options (plus clear via X when allowed).
5. **Filter bars** — Prefer `All` / `Any …` for “no filter”, not `— Select —`. Keep those labels.
6. **Implementation** — Prefer shared `Select` from `components/forms/Inputs.tsx` (auto-injects placeholder + smart open-on-click). Do not invent one-off dropdown chrome.

```tsx
<Select value={vendorId} onChange={…}>
  <option value="">— Select —</option>
  {vendors.map((v) => (
    <option key={v.id} value={v.id}>{v.vendorName}</option>
  ))}
</Select>
```
